==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ideality
<hw>I`de*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Idealities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality
or state of being ideal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The capacity to form ideals of beauty or
perfection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Phren.)</fld> <def>The conceptive
faculty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idealization</ent>⟦br⟧
